result.execSummary:
The defendant Moises Del Valle Castellanos was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Moises Del Valle Castellanos is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Moises Del Valle Castellanos was found guilty of Battery, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Moises Del Valle Castellanos was found guilty of Criminal Damage to Property, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

11:22 a.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty Roberto Ledesma.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Interpreter sworn.  Statement by Atty Ledesma, recites agreement, defendant will plea to count 1 and count 2, dismissing the domestic enhancer.  State concurs.  Defendant concurs.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.

Defendant enters a plea of GUILTY.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty on counts 1 & 2.  Court orders count 3 be dismissed and count 4 be dismissed and read-in.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  DA confirms compliance with victim witness rights.  Sentencing statement by DA.  Sentencing statement by Atty Ledesma.  Statement by the defendant.  Court orders the domestic enhancer be dismissed.

Court sentences the defendant to: 

COUNT 1 (Battery) - 9 months county jail, stayed and places the defendant on probation for 2 years.
COUNT 2 (CDTP) - SWD, and place the defendant on probation for 2 years.

CONDITIONS: (EACH COUNT)

-AODA and any follow-up
-Ct 1- 6 months county jail, with huber and to commence within 60 days.  Court grants out of county service and out of county travel.
-Court costs.
-Defendant is to maintain absolute sobriety - not to possess or consume any alcohol, illegal drugs or prescription drugs without a valid prescription.
-No Contact with the victim.  Forms of no contact include: in person, in writing, by telephone, by e-mail, or by any other forms of electronic communication, or through a third party intending to circumvent the no contact provision.
-Defendant is to submit a DNA Sample.

Court orders any cash bond on file be applied to the court costs.

Court adjourned at 11:42 a.m.
